Then you must loop over all Strings when displaying so will display all of them. Your loop was just iterating over the first element.

Also, when adding a name you must add it and not overwrite the first one. If you want to return to your selection, you need to use a loop.

The following code should work, but I think you should get to know basic control structures before starting to code.

```
public static void main (String[] args) {
    LinkedList&lt;String&gt; nameList = new LinkedList&lt;String&gt;();

    while (true) {  // Repeat forever
        int choice = Integer.parseInt(JOptionPane.showInputDialog(&quot;[1] Insert Name\n[2] Display Names&quot;));

        if (choice == 1) 
            nameList.add(JOptionPane.showInputDialog(&quot;Insert Your Name: &quot;));

        if (choice == 2) 
            for (String name: nameList)  // loop over all strings in the list
                JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, &quot;Name: &quot;+ name);
    }
}
```

Note however, that you need to `import java.util.LinkedList;` for this to work.

